Subject: [PATCH] ToolBarPageHeader: set topPadding/bottomPadding to 0

The comment already says "pageRow.globalToolBar.*Height already include
the paddings", so AbstractApplicationHeader should not subtract additional
topPadding/bottomPadding from the content area. Setting them to 0 makes
mainItem fill the full toolbar height, ensuring toolbar content is
properly vertically centered.
---
 src/controls/private/globaltoolbar/ToolBarPageHeader.qml | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/controls/private/globaltoolbar/ToolBarPageHeader.qml b/src/controls/private/globaltoolbar/ToolBarPageHeader.qml
index bb9f70d1..39445f68 100644
--- a/src/controls/private/globaltoolbar/ToolBarPageHeader.qml
+++ b/src/controls/private/globaltoolbar/ToolBarPageHeader.qml
@@ -34,6 +34,8 @@ Kirigami.AbstractApplicationHeader {
 
     leftPadding: Kirigami.Units.mediumSpacing
     rightPadding: Kirigami.Units.mediumSpacing
+    topPadding: 0
+    bottomPadding: 0
 
     MouseArea {
         anchors.fill: parent
